    "headline": "High-Value Home Sales Are Exposing a Tax-Planning Gap for Sellers, MetLife Poll Finds",
    "summary": "NEW YORK, July 07, 2026--Rising property values are turning many high-value home sales into tax-planning events, with sellers facing larger capital gains and looking to real estate professionals for guidance before a deal closes. MetLife’s 2026 Structured Installment Sales Poll finds that real estate brokers and agents see a growing need to help clients understand the financial implications of a sale, as many sellers are not comfortable making complex tax and planning decisions on their own.",
